<?xml version='1.0' encoding='utf-8'?>
<Weakness xmlns="http://cwe.mitre.org/cwe-7" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" ID="506" Name="Embedded Malicious Code" Abstraction="Class" Structure="Simple" Status="Incomplete">
         <Description>The product contains code that appears to be malicious in nature.</Description>
         <Extended_Description>Malicious flaws have acquired colorful names, including Trojan horse, trapdoor, timebomb, and logic-bomb. A developer might insert malicious code with the intent to subvert the security of a product or its host system at some time in the future. It generally refers to a program that performs a useful service but exploits rights of the program's user in a way the user does not intend.</Extended_Description>
